@startuml 16.5_replyCommentBlog
hide footbox
title Reply Comment Blog

actor User
boundary CommentBlogPage as View
control CommentBlogRoute as Route
participant ":AuthMiddleware" as Middleware
control "CommentBlogController" as Controller
participant ":CommentBlogService" as Service
participant ":CommentBlogModel" as Model
database Database as Database

User -> View : 1. Click "Reply" on a comment
activate View
View -> View : 2. Open reply box\n(input reply content)

User -> View : 3. Enter reply content and submit
View -> View : 4. Validate reply input\n(not empty, max length)

opt Check validation
    View --> User : 4.1. Show validation error
end

    View -> Route : 5. POST /blogs/{blogId}/comments/{commentId}/replies
    activate Route

    Route -> Middleware : 6. AuthenticateUser(req, res, next)
    activate Middleware
    Middleware --> Route : 7. Authentication success
    Middleware -> Controller : 8. Forward ReplyCommentBlogRequest\n(blogId, commentId, content)
    deactivate Middleware
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Service : 9. Process reply comment
    activate Service

alt Parent comment not found
    Service -> Model : 9.1. Validate parent comment
    activate Model

    Model -> Database : 9.1.1. Retrieve parent comment by ID
    activate Database
    Database --> Model : 9.1.2. Result (null)
    deactivate Database

    Model --> Service : 9.1.3. Return not found
    deactivate Model

        Service --> Controller : 9.1.4. Return not found result
        Controller --> Route : 9.1.5. Return 404 Not Found + message
        Route --> View : 9.1.6. Show error: "Comment not found"
else Parent comment exists
        Service -> Model : 9.2. Save reply comment
        activate Model

        Model -> Database : 9.2.1. Persist reply data\n(parentCommentId, userId, content)
        activate Database
        Database --> Model : 9.2.2. Created
        deactivate Database

        Model --> Service : 9.2.3. Return created reply entity
        deactivate Model

        Service --> Controller : 9.2.4. Return ReplyCommentBlogResponse
        deactivate Service
        Controller --> Route : 9.2.5. Return 200 OK + reply data
        deactivate Controller
        Route --> View : 9.2.6. Render reply under parent comment
        deactivate Route
end

View --> User : 10. Display result (reply posted or error)
deactivate View
@enduml
